                            <comment id="441438" author="adilger" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 01:11:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=wamax&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;wamax&quot;&gt;wamax&lt;/a&gt;, it looks like your patch has fixed a number of failed subtests in pjdfstests subtest &lt;tt&gt;chown_00&lt;/tt&gt;, but there are still a small number of failures left that prevent that subtest from being enabled by default, as described in my last comment in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12922&quot; title=&quot;pjdfstest chown_00: POSIX compliance failed on lustre&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12922&quot;&gt;LU-12922&lt;/a&gt;.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The remaining &lt;tt&gt;chown_00&lt;/tt&gt; failures are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt; not ok 312 - tried &apos;-u 65532 -g 65531 -- chown pjdfstest_0a7af -1 -1&apos;, expected 0, got EPERM
 not ok 319 - tried &apos;-u 65532 -g 65531 -- chown pjdfstest_0a7afe -1 -1&apos;, expected 0, got EPERM
 not ok 327 - tried &apos;-u 65532 -g 65531 -- lchown pjdfstest_0a7af -1 -1&apos;, expected 0, got EPERM
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I&apos;m reading this correctly, it looks like we are returning &lt;tt&gt;EPERM&lt;/tt&gt; when &lt;tt&gt;chown(FILE, -1, -1)&lt;/tt&gt; is called (i.e. &quot;do nothing&quot;).  It would be great if you could fix that issue as well, so that the &lt;tt&gt;chown_00&lt;/tt&gt; subtest could be enabled and catch any potential regressions in the future.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="441276" author="gerrit" created="Wed, 15 Jan 2025 22:05:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;&quot;Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch:&lt;/del&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/57788&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/57788&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
