                            <comment id="440836" author="adilger" created="Sat, 11 Jan 2025 17:50:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was checking the &lt;a href=&quot;https://linux.die.net/man/2/chown&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;chown(2)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt; man page:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The owner of a file may change the group of the file to any group of which that owner is a member.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;so it doesn&apos;t mention anything about write permissions, so this seems reasonable. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
